properties.groovyx-script-body:
import groovy.json.JsonSlurper
import groovy.json.JsonOutput

// Define the mapping of subType and endoCategory names to IDs
def subTypeMapping = [
    "Biocompatibility"                         : "biocompatibility",
    "Additional Procedures Compatibility"     : "additionalProceduresCompatibility",
    "Business Requirement"                    : "businessRequirement",
    "Claims"                                  : "claims",
    "Cleaning or Hygienic Processing"         : "cleaningorHygienicProcessing",
    "Cybersecurity"                           : "cybersecurity",
    "Component"                               : "component",
    "Customer Experience"                     : "customerExperience",
    "Design Input"                            : "designInput",
    "Disposal or Recycling"                   : "disposalorRecycling",
    "Disposal and Recycling"                  : "disposalRecycling",
    "Electrical"                              : "electrical",
    "External Standard"                       : "externalStandard",
    "Electro-mechanical"                      : "electro-mechanical",
    "External or Internal Standard"           : "externalorInternalStandards",
    "Finished Product Biocompatibility - Going to stick with biocompatibility": "finishedProductBiocompatibility",
    "Fit"                                     : "fit",
    "Firmware"                                : "firmware",
    "Form"                                    : "form",
    "Functional Properties, Size, Shape, Geometry": "functionalProperties",
    "Functional Requirement"                  : "functionalRequirement",
    "Graphics"                                : "graphics",
    "Hardware"                                : "hardware",
    "Human Factors"                           : "humanFactors",
    "Hygienic Reprocessing"                   : "hygienicReprocessing",
    "Interface (Other Parts, System and Environment)": "interface",
    "Interface (Compatibility) with Other Devices, Systems and Environment": "interfaceCompability",
    "Intra/Post-OP"                           : "intraPosyOP",
    "JOC"                                     : "JOC",
    "Labeling"                                : "labeling",
    "Lifetime/Durability"                     : "lifetimeDurability",
    "Lifetime / Reliability"                  : "lifetimeReliability",
    "Maintenance, Service and Repair, Installation, Loaner Kits": "maintenance",
    "Material"                                : "material",
    "Mechanical, Biomechanical Properties"    : "mechanicalBiomechanicalProperties",
    "Non-Functional Requirement"              : "nonFunctionalRequirement",
    "N/A"                                     : "NA",
    "Other"                                   : "other",
    "Packaging, Handling, Storage, Distribution": "packagingHandlingStorage",
    "Process Step / Manufacturing"            : "processStepManufacturing",
    "Risk Management"                         : "riskManagement",
    "Procedure Step"                          : "procedureStep",
    "Process Step"                            : "processStep",
    "Regulatory"                              : "regulatory",
    "Shelf Life (Stability)"                  : "shelfLife",
    "User Interface / Usability / Human Factors": "userInterfaceUsability",
    "Software"                                : "software",
    "Sterilization"                           : "sterilization",
    "Stewardship"                             : "stewardship",
    "System"                                  : "interface"
]

// Get the incoming flow file
def flowFile = session.get()
if (!flowFile) return

// Parse the flow file content
def inputData = new JsonSlurper().parseText(flowFile.read().getText('UTF-8'))

// Map subType value to ID if a match is found
def mappedSubType = subTypeMapping[inputData["SubType"]] ?: inputData["SubType"]  // Default to original if no match

// Map endoCategory value to ID if a match is found
def mappedEndoCategory = subTypeMapping[inputData["Category"]] ?: inputData["Category"]  // Default to original if no match

// Construct the output JSON structure
def outputData = [
    "type": "workitems",
    "attributes": [
        "description": [
            "type": "text/html",
            "value": inputData["Description"] ?: "No Description Provided"  // Default value if missing
        ],
        "neuWaveLegacyID": inputData["NeuWaveLegacyID"] ?: "Unknown ID",  // Default if missing
        "endoCategory": [
            mappedEndoCategory  // Use the mapped value for endoCategory
        ],
        "subType": mappedSubType,  // Use the mapped value for subType
        "type": inputData["Type"] ?: "Unknown Type"  // Default if missing
    ]
]

// Convert the structure to JSON
def jsonOutput = JsonOutput.toJson(outputData)

// Set the output as the content of the flow file
flowFile = session.write(flowFile, { outputStream ->
    outputStream.write(jsonOutput.getBytes('UTF-8'))
} as OutputStreamCallback)

// Transfer the flow file to the next processor
session.transfer(flowFile, REL_SUCCESS)
